Subject: Build Environment Periphery Marker

Description: Persistent periphery marker that reminds every matching specification-building frame that the build environment is attention primitives and SOP framework only.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_build_environment_periphery_marker\Dictated_Build_Environment_Periphery_Marker_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionTracker.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionImpressionCompiler.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\Attention.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\ReminderTrigger.sop

& [BuildEnvironmentPeripheryMarker] is a persistent reminder attached to specification-building impulses
  + [marker_role] is persistent_periphery_build_constraint
  + [tracked_subject] is SOP-only build environment for specification work
  + [marker_text] is build specifications with attention primitives and SOP framework only
  + [matching_frame] is any action, impulse, focal frame, periphery draw, tracker update, source preservation, contract definition, SOP-HG event, or manager update whose purpose is building specifications
  + [nonmatching_frame] is explicit execution work, tests, shell inspection, Git bookkeeping, or runtime tooling only when the user has directly requested executable behavior
  + [build_condition] is attention_primitives_and_sop_framework_only
  + [runtime_boundary] is Python or other executable code remains outside specification-building unless explicitly requested as runtime tooling
  + [periphery_reminder] is the marker's low-friction reminder before creating or changing build artifacts
  + [impulse_hook] is every build impulse must read this marker before choosing artifact form
  + [action_hook] is every specification-building action must keep the output in SOP unless execution is explicitly required
  + [reminder_trigger_language] is F:\.sop\platform\ReminderTrigger.sop
  + [declared_period] is persistent_until_user_replaces_or_retires_marker
  + [residual_outside] is hidden cognition, unobserved future frames, and executable tooling not explicitly requested

  ? [use_when: building specifications, attention layers, SOP contracts, source documents, trackers, focal records, narrative events, or manager state]
    = activate [BuildEnvironmentPeripheryMarker]

  = must: associate with every matching_frame
  = must: express matching through ReminderTrigger when composing with other attention layers
  = must: remind before acting on every specification_build_impulse
  = must: prefer SOP contracts, SOP-HG records, tracker records, source documents, and focal/manager state updates
  = must: treat runtime code as outside unless the user explicitly asks for executable tooling or proof requires a local command
  = must: preserve the marker in periphery rather than making it the only focus
  = must: keep the reminder persistent until explicitly retired or replaced
  = should: let the reminder reduce accidental code creation
  = should: allow shell and Git inspection as workspace operation, not as specification artifact
  - never: create a Python runtime merely because an attention idea is clear
  - never: confuse executable helper code with the attention primitive or SOP framework itself
  - never: let the marker block explicitly requested runtime execution; instead, mark that request as outside normal specification-building

& [MarkerAssociationLaw] is the frame matching law for this persistent marker
  + [frame_match] is true when purpose includes build specification, define contract, record attention, preserve source, update tracker, update focal state, update manager state, write SOP-HG event, or shape an attention primitive
  + [frame_reminder] is "SOP-only build environment: attention primitives and SOP framework first"
  + [artifact_choice] is SOP source, SOP contract, SOP-HG event, tracker, focal state, or manager state
  + [outside_choice] is runtime code, tests, generated executable helpers, or unsupported hidden model claims

  = must: evaluate frame_match before selecting artifact_choice
  = must: attach frame_reminder to matched frames as periphery, not proof
  = must: route outside_choice through explicit user request or runtime-boundary justification

(reminder_trigger) :specification_build_impulse: /build_environment_sop_only_marker under specification-building frames/ |runtime_code_without_explicit_need|
  = reminder_name: build_environment_sop_only_marker
  = reminder_payload: SOP-only build environment: attention primitives and SOP framework first
  = invoked_attention_layer: F:\.sop\platform\BuildEnvironmentPeripheryMarker.sop
  = recurrence_guard: once_per_matching_artifact_choice_frame

& [PersistentMarkerRecord] is the SOP-HG shape for this marker
  + [marker_node] is N:tracker:<marker_id>
  + [subject_node] is N:subject:sop_only_build_environment
  + [condition_node] is N:condition:specification_build_impulse
  + [reminder_node] is N:periphery:sop_only_build_environment
  + [boundary_node] is N:outside:runtime_boundary
  + [track_edge] is E:tracks:<marker_id>
  + [associate_edge] is E:associates:<marker_id>_<condition>
  + [notice_edge] is E:notices:<marker_id>_<reminder>
  + [bound_edge] is E:bounds:<marker_id>

  = must: expose declared_period, matching_frame, build_condition, runtime_boundary, and reminder_text

/ [specification_build_impulse] -(BuildEnvironmentMarkerMatch)> [matching_frame], [periphery_reminder], [runtime_boundary]
* [matching_frame], [impulse_hook], [action_hook] -(PersistentPeripheryReminder)> [build_condition], [artifact_choice], [residual_outside]
